# Chapter 10: Building a Simple AI Chatbot

*In which we write actual code and end up with something real.*

---

## What We're Building

By the end of this chapter, you'll have a working backend API that:
- Accepts a user message and a chunk of text
- Generates quiz questions from the text using AI
- Returns structured JSON that a frontend can display

This is the core engine of the Study Buddy app. It has no frontend yet — that's Chapter 11. Right now we're building the brains.

---

## Project Structure

Let's set up the project properly:

```bash
mkdir study-buddy
cd study-buddy
npm init -y
npm install openai express dotenv cors
```

Create the folder structure:

```
study-buddy/
├── src/
│   ├── index.js        # Express server entry point
│   ├── routes/
│   │   └── quiz.js     # Quiz generation route
│   └── prompts/
│       └── system.js   # System prompt (kept separate for easy iteration)
├── .env                # Your API keys
├── .gitignore
└── package.json
```

Update `package.json`:
```json
{
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node src/index.js",
    "dev": "node --watch src/index.js"
  }
}
```

`.gitignore`:
```
node_modules/
.env
```

`.env`:
```
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
PORT=3001
```

---

## The System Prompt

Keep your system prompt in its own file — it will change frequently as you iterate:

```javascript
// src/prompts/system.js
export const STUDY_BUDDY_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `
You are StudyBuddy, an expert AI tutor specialized in generating 
effective quiz questions to help students learn.

When given a passage of text, generate exactly 5 multiple-choice 
questions that test genuine comprehension of the material.

Requirements:
- Each question must have 4 options (A, B, C, D) with exactly one correct answer
- Questions should test understanding, not just memorization
- Only use information from the provided text — no outside knowledge
- Include a brief, clear explanation for the correct answer
- Make questions challenging but fair

Respond with valid JSON in exactly this format:
{
  "questions": [
    {
      "question": "...",
      "options": {
        "A": "...",
        "B": "...",
        "C": "...",
        "D": "..."
      },
      "correct": "A",
      "explanation": "..."
    }
  ]
}

If the provided text is too short or not meaningful, respond with:
{
  "error": "The provided text is too short to generate meaningful questions. Please paste at least a few paragraphs."
}
`.trim();
```

---

## The Express Server

```javascript
// src/index.js
import 'dotenv/config';
import express from 'express';
import cors from 'cors';
import { quizRouter } from './routes/quiz.js';

const app = express();
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3001;

// Middleware
app.use(express.json());
app.use(cors());  // Allows frontend to call this API

// Routes
app.use('/api', quizRouter);

// Health check endpoint
app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});

// Start server
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`StudyBuddy API running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});
```

---

## The Quiz Route

This is where the real work happens:

```javascript
// src/routes/quiz.js
import express from 'express';
import OpenAI from 'openai';
import { STUDY_BUDDY_SYSTEM_PROMPT } from '../prompts/system.js';

export const quizRouter = express.Router();

const client = new OpenAI({
  apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
});

// Input validation constants
const MAX_INPUT_LENGTH = 8000;   // ~2000 words
const MIN_INPUT_LENGTH = 100;    // At least a paragraph

quizRouter.post('/generate-quiz', async (req, res) => {
  const { text } = req.body;

  // --- Input Validation ---
  if (!text || typeof text !== 'string') {
    return res.status(400).json({ 
      error: 'Missing or invalid "text" field in request body.' 
    });
  }

  const trimmedText = text.trim();

  if (trimmedText.length < MIN_INPUT_LENGTH) {
    return res.status(400).json({ 
      error: 'Text is too short. Please provide at least a paragraph.' 
    });
  }

  if (trimmedText.length > MAX_INPUT_LENGTH) {
    return res.status(400).json({ 
      error: `Text is too long. Please limit to ${MAX_INPUT_LENGTH} characters.` 
    });
  }

  // --- Call the AI ---
  try {
    const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
      model: 'gpt-4o',
      messages: [
        { 
          role: 'system', 
          content: STUDY_BUDDY_SYSTEM_PROMPT 
        },
        { 
          role: 'user', 
          content: `Please generate quiz questions from this text:\n\n${trimmedText}` 
        }
      ],
      response_format: { type: 'json_object' },
      temperature: 0.3,  // Low temp for consistent, focused output
    });

    // --- Parse and Validate Response ---
    let result;
    try {
      result = JSON.parse(completion.choices[0].message.content);
    } catch (parseError) {
      console.error('Failed to parse AI response:', completion.choices[0].message.content);
      return res.status(500).json({ 
        error: 'AI returned invalid JSON. Please try again.' 
      });
    }

    // Check if AI returned an error message
    if (result.error) {
      return res.status(400).json(result);
    }

    // Return the quiz along with token usage for debugging
    return res.json({
      ...result,
      _meta: {
        model: completion.model,
        tokensUsed: completion.usage.total_tokens,
      }
    });

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('OpenAI API error:', error);

    if (error.status === 429) {
      return res.status(429).json({ 
        error: 'Rate limit exceeded. Please wait a moment and try again.' 
      });
    }

    if (error.status === 401) {
      return res.status(500).json({ 
        error: 'API authentication failed. Contact support.' 
      });
    }

    return res.status(500).json({ 
      error: 'Something went wrong. Please try again.' 
    });
  }
});
```

